get.description:
Returns a list of supported authentication providers. You can use these
providers with the sessions API.

Retrieves the current cluster configuration. Requires a user with at least
the *admin_view* permission. See https://kb.vmware.com/kb/2123058

parameters.name: defaults
parameters.description: Include all un-specified configuration options and their default values too.

put.description:
Sets a new internal cluster configuration.
Configuration is replicated internally to all cluster members.
Some configuration options require a service restart to take effect.
Option values modified using one of these methods are not checked for validity.
Confirm all changes before applying them.

parameters.name: validate
parameters.description:
Whether to perform limited validation on the new configuration blob.
Default of `true` is highly recommended.

400.description:
Failed to apply configuration changes, either because of a parse error
or invalid configuration options.

parameters.name: Authorization
parameters.description:
The standard HTTP Authorization header includes the keyword Bearer
and the sessionId value returned from the POST `/sessions` API.

post.description:
Signs into Log Insight with the given credentials, created and returns a
new session.

401.description: Could not sign in with the given credentials.

503.description: Log Insight did not have its initial configuration set up yet.

get.description: Retrieve Log Insight version information, in the form Major.Minor.Patch-Build.
